In this project, the C++ program that reads a text file and counts how many times each word appears. 
The file used is a short Sherlock Holmes passage.
The program basically opens a file called homes.txt, reads all the words, sorts them, and then
counts how many times each word shows up. Finally, it prints each word with its count. 
The functions used:
getWords: this function reads words from the file and stores them in a vector. 
sortWords: this function sorts all the words alphabetically.
getWordCounts: this function counts how many times each word appears and stores the result as a word and a number. 
